                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            
    
<p>Van Gogh and <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_663">Salles</rs> left according to schedule on Wednesday, 8 May 1889 for the asylum of Saint-Paul-de-Mausole in Saint-Rémy. Van Gogh’s name was recorded on that date in <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Le grand registre de l’asile de Saint-Rémy</hi>. <ref xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" target="documentation.xml#id8May1889">See <hi rend="italics">Documentation</hi>, 8 May 1889</ref>. </p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>On Monday, 29 April <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_663">Salles</rs> had had a talk with <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_568">Dr Peyron</rs> about Vincent’s admission to the asylum. <ref xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" target="let763.xml">See letter 763</ref>, <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Date</hi>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
